Aggregated index diagnosis

This is to investigate the relationships between original and aggregated indexes, and across aggregated indexes, with or without comparison with a benchmark index, to evaluate how well aggregated indexes represent their own cluster.

Correlation

The ideal outcome is that the majority of the correlations of original indexes with their corresonding aggregated indexes are higher than the correlations of original indexes with a benchmark index.
